oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Bluebird 78's - tape 6
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Tape 6 of recordings of Bluebird 78 discs, featuring Joe's Acadians (performers), The Four Aces (performers), Happy Fats and his Rayne-Bo Ramblers (performers), Jean Fuselier (performer), and the Hackberry Ramblers (performers), performing Creole tunes from the 1930's.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Joe's Acadians; The Four Aces; Happy Fats and his Rayne-Bo Ramblers; Jean Fuselier; Hackberry Ramblers
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dcterms:tableOfContents: Test tones -- J'vas Tamey Camine (Hackberry Ramblers) -- La Valse De La Prison (Hackberry Ramblers) -- Vous Me Fois Espere (The Four Aces) -- Que Ces Que Ma Chere (The Four Aces) -- Fille De La Compaigne (Jean Fuselier) -- Ma Chere Bouclett (Jean Fuselier) -- Il Ya Pas La Claire De Lune (Joe's Acadians) -- La Fille De Village (Joe's Acadians) -- Escue Te Maime (Happy Fats and his Rayne-Bo Ramblers)
